<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <title>Create — ADMESH-Domains</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Coming soon: tools for authoring ADCIRC mesh files in the browser." />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css" />
</head>
<body>
  <header id="site-header"></header>
  <main>
    <h1>Create &mdash; Coming Soon</h1>
    <p>The Create tab is under construction. The plan is to bring mesh-authoring into the browser:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Click-a-waterbody</strong> &mdash; SAM-style segmentation: click a lake or coastline on a basemap and the boundary is extracted into a fort.14 outline.
        Tracking: <a href="https://github.com/domattioli/ADMESH-Domains/issues/1" target="_blank" rel="noopener">issue #1</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>Freehand draw &rarr; fort.14</strong> &mdash; sketch a polygon, get a starter mesh.
        Tracking: <a href="https://github.com/domattioli/ADMESH-Domains/issues/2" target="_blank" rel="noopener">issue #2</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>Natural-language prompts</strong> &mdash; describe a domain in English, get a mesh draft.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>For now, you can drop a mesh file below and the page will run the existing client-side parser
      and print the results to the mock terminal. Use it to sanity-check a mesh before contributing it.</p>

    <label for="file" class="dropzone" id="dropzone">
      <strong>Drop a mesh file</strong> or click to choose
      <input id="file" type="file" accept=".14,.grd,.2dm,.fort" hidden />
    </label>

    <h2 style="margin-top:1.5rem;">Console</h2>
    <pre id="terminal" class="terminal" aria-live="polite"><span class="muted">$ admesh-create&nbsp;ready &mdash; awaiting file...</span></pre>

    <p class="muted">Want to suggest a feature? <a href="feedback.html">Open a feedback issue</a>.</p>
  </main>
  <footer id="site-footer"></footer>
  <script type="module" src="js/create.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
